The paper discusses the design and implementation of an FPGA accelerator for training convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of an automatic compiler to generate FPGA-synthesizable RTL also suggests a focus on computer-aided design (cs.AR) and hardware architecture (cs.AR, cs.ET). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of optimized RTL libraries and a cyclic weight storage/access scheme, which are related to digital circuits and systems (cs.DC) and embedded systems (cs.SY).
